{{Infobox stadium | name = Geolog Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Geolog stadium - Tyumen.jpg | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Tyumen]], [[Russia]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = 1982 | opened = 1983 | renovated = 2011 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = [[Artificial turf]] | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 13,057 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = [[FC Tyumen]], [[FC Ural]] (2014-2015) | embedded = | website = }}
'''Geolog Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Tyumen]], [[Russia]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[FC Tyumen]]. The stadium holds 13,057 people, all seated. Since 2008, many health units including a sports hall and gymnasium, swimming pool, saunas, and a restaurant, have been added to the complex.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www3.traxontechnologies.com/showcase/showcase_details/14187|title=Geolog Stadium - Tyumen, Russia|website=Traxon - e:cue}}</ref>
