{{Unreferenced|date=April 2013}} {{Infobox Stadium | name = Sirens Stadium | nickname = | image =<!-- [[File:Sirens Stadium.jpg|250px]] --> | caption = | fullname = | location = {{Flagicon|Malta}} [[St. Paul's Bay]], [[Malta]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1970 (sandy pitch) | renovated = 2011 (new pitch Artificial Turf) | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Sirens F.C.]] | operator = [[Sirens F.C.]] | surface = Artificial Turf | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[Sirens F.C.]] | capacity = 600 | dimensions = | scoreboard = }} The '''Sirens Stadium''' is a stadium in [[St. Paul's Bay]], [[Malta]]. It opened in 2011 as Artificial Turf (properly open 1970 as sandy pitch). It is the home ground of Maltese football club [[Sirens F.C.]], who currently play in the [[Maltese FA Trophy]], [[Maltese Second Division]] and [[Maltese Third Division]]. It is used for matches from the Maltese FA Trophy, Maltese Third Division, Maltese Second Division and even [[friendly match|Exhibition game]]. It is also used by all the [[Sirens F.C.]] teams from the youth teams up until the senior teams for training. It holds 600 people on the stadium. <!-- [[File:Old Sirens Stadium.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Old Sirens Stadium]] -->
